## Steps

### step 1
id: find-profile-link
instruction: At the very bottom of the left sidebar, below a divider line, you'll see your name and role. Click on your name or avatar to open your profile settings.
success_criteria: You are on the Profile page. A left-side menu shows sections: General, Security, Organization, and (if admin) Providers and Team.
anchor: "profile link"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Scroll to the bottom of the sidebar. Your profile link is below all main navigation sections, under a horizontal divider.

### step 2
id: review-general-settings
instruction: The General tab is selected by default. You can see your name (editable via the pencil icon), your email (read-only), and your sign-in method.
success_criteria: You can see your profile information.
anchor: "General"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Click "General" in the left menu if needed.

### step 3
id: update-or-explore
instruction: Click the pencil icon next to your name to edit it. Or explore other sections: Security to change your password, Organization for org-level settings, Team (admin only) to invite users and manage roles.
success_criteria: You have made any desired changes and explored available settings.
anchor: "edit icon"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Click the pencil/edit icon next to your name. Type the new name and press Enter or click the checkmark.

## Completion Message
profile settings are yours to manage. if you're an admin, the Team section is where you invite new users and assign roles.

